CAPE TOWN - Wriddhiman Saha became the first Indian wicketkeeper to make ten dismissals in a Test match when he held five catches in South Africa's second innings on the fourth day of the first Test at Newlands on Monday. Saha also took five catches in the first innings. LIVE UPDATES: SA v India, 1st Test, Day 4Â  He broke the record held by Mahendra Singh Dhoni, who made nine dismissals, with eight catches and a stumping, against Australia in Melbourne in 2014/15. AFP